snippet.textDisplay:
This song is like a wave. It's a journey. Like in the beginning of a journey, you are so enthusiastic, full of energy, optimistic. That feeling is covered by the first singer. 
Then it's like there's a storm in the way, your path seems to be never ending, it's infinite, it's blurred. You are facing too many problems. But, you have to made it till the end even if you have to die. That part being covered by Shilpa. 
And then again some divine mercy is bestowed in your heart. Your faith on the divine gets multiplied by thousand folds. You know your master will never leave you in this hour of turmoil. You start believing somehow you will cover that distance by the grace of Almighty. "*jaida tenu paar lagawe*" . That part being taken up by the last singer. 
Love, respect and many congratulations for making a lifetime track that will be listened, cherished and appreciated by many generations ahead. 
From India.
